About
Stunning 360-degree views 240 meters above the world-famous Palm Jumeirah. At 240 meters high, The View on level 52 of the iconic Palm Tower offers panoramic, 360-degree views of Palm Jumeirah, the Arabian Gulf, and beyond from an outdoor terrace and a premium lounge. Spot iconic landmarks and hidden gems of this beautiful city.

    A great evening out learning about the creation of Palm Island and top tier views
    We visited The View at the Palm during a 10 day stay in Dubai stopping at the famous Atlantis the Palm. From Atlantis is was easy to reach on the metro to Nakheel Mall then taking the elevator to the top. We went at night time but we have said if we come again we would like to go in the day too. The 360 views are amazing. If you have a nervous disposition to heights this probably isn't for you but try and push through it like my husband did as it will be worth it. Even I felt wobbly standing on some of the glass platforms! You can buy professional photos at the end. Staff are really friendly and our daughter enjoyed running around. Was also interesting learning about the history of Palm island and the creation of it before you go out to the viewing deck. All in all, a good evening out. Also food and drinks outlets there.
    Nakheel

  • Hana
    Cambridge, United Kingdom24 contributions
    Best View of Palm Jumeirah
    Amazing view of the iconic Palm Jumeirah. I think this is the best view of the island, which you cannot get anywhere else. We went to the queue quite early so we did not have to wait long. The Nakheel mall is also very accessible and the entrance to the top deck is very easy to navigate, as they have an in-house online map which you can get when you scan the QR code at the mall entrance. However, even though it was September at that time, and according to the locals, the temperature is a bit better, it was still boiling hot at the top deck. The official souvenir photographer took us to the rooftop and asked us to do lying and sitting poses, touching the sweltering hot surface. I liked the photos though, only because of the view (my face looked like I was burning) so I bought them. I was really surprised to find that they were really expensive! I was not going to buy them because of the price but (A) I felt obliged since the photographer took many photos (maybe almost a hundred) and (B) you cannot get the few photos you like unless you pay for the whole package! Upon checking my online banking I felt a deep regret as I spent £67 for photos!! It came in a nice frame though but I still felt cheated. I know it's not their fault because they told us the price before they showed us the photos at the shop (not before they took them) but it was not a nice experience for me paying that much for what I expected to be a reasonable price. The photos were more expensive than the entrance fee itself. Anyway I cannot take that money back now but I brought back memories (the good and the bad!) with me and I will forever remember that moment where I was at the top, seeing the view of the Palm.
